import Dregg2.Crypto.UcSignature -- the LAST protocol game, closing the crypto tree into ONE connected proof: REVOCATION SOUNDNESS (token/src/revocation.rs GAP #5 — you cannot pass a revoked token off as un-revoked). REUSES HybridCombiner's SigScheme/Forgery/EufCma AND HermineHintMLWE's HashCR carrier verbatim — no new carrier. Model: the revocation tree is a CommitReveal Unit (Finset Id) Digest whose H () s is the Merkle root of the revoked set s (HashCR = the root binds its member set, the abstraction of SortedRevocationTree::root's blake3 fold); the client accepts id as un-revoked iff an Absent witness opens the root to a set omitting id (the NonMembershipProof denotation); an AttestedRoot(root,epoch,sig) carries the authority's SigScheme signature over (root‖epoch), verifyAttested = SigScheme.verify under the ENROLLED key. TWO DOORS, both closed by a named carrier: (1) merkle_root_binds + revoked_cannot_prove_absence — under HashCR a valid absence for a revoked id against its own honestly-attested root IS a hash collision (you can't hide a revocation); (2) forged_attestation_is_a_signature_forgery — an accepted-but-unsigned root is a Forgery on the authority key, and wrong_root_for_epoch_is_forgery makes stale-root replay a forgery (epoch signed INSIDE the body). DICHOTOMY forged_non_revocation_breaks_cr_or_forges: a client accepting a revoked id ⇒ ¬HashCR ∨ Forgery (mirrors CapabilityChain.chain_forgery's case split; HonestAttestation = the honestDelegation analogue). HEADLINE revocation_sound_under_floor: with the per-key forking reductions, no revoked id is accepted provided HashCR ∧ (SchnorrDLHard ∨ MSISHard) — EufCma DISCHARGED by HybridCombiner.hybrid_secure_if_either_floor, so the last game bottoms out at the SAME DL/lattice floors as the whole tree. Teeth (a) binding: honest non-revoked id ACCEPTED, revoked id has NO absence (HashCR fires), colliding tree HIDES the revocation (HashCR load-bearing); (b) attestation (toy sig=pk+m): attacker-key REJECTED, accepted-but-unsigned root EXHIBITS the Forgery. #assert_all_clean (19 keystones).
