import Dregg2.Crypto.DowngradeResistance -- the POST-QUANTUM NEGOTIATION game riding the HybridCombiner keystone: DOWNGRADE RESISTANCE (an active MITM cannot force two honest parties onto a WEAKER classical-only cipher suite than both support — exactly the PQ threat model). REUSES HybridCombiner's SigScheme/Forgery/EufCma verbatim — no new carrier. Model: Suite carries a strength preorder (Classical < Hybrid); IsStrongestCommon a b s = s is in both supported sets and ≥ every common member (unique by antisymmetry, strongest_common_unique). The handshake is AUTHENTICATED: a SignedTranscript records both supported sets + the negotiated suite, each party signs the body (aSup‖bSup‖neg) and VERIFIES the peer's signature before accepting (AAccepts/BAccepts, each also pins its OWN supported set intact). HonestSigner (the HonestAttestation analogue) = an honest party signs ONLY a body recording its true set and the strongest-common negotiated suite. REDUCTION downgrade_forces_forgery: if A accepts neg STRICTLY WEAKER than the true strongest-common best, then had B signed it HonestSigner+uniqueness force neg=best (contra neg<best), so the accepted transcript B never signed IS a SigScheme.Forgery on B's key. HEADLINE downgrade_resistant: under B's EufCma no MITM makes BOTH accept a suite < best. ANCHOR downgrade_resistant_under_floor ("you can't strip the PQ"): with the per-key forking reductions, EufCma is DISCHARGED by HybridCombiner.hybrid_secure_if_either_floor from SchnorrDLHard ∨ MSISHard — so even a QUANTUM adversary that broke ed25519 (SchnorrDLHard falls) still faces MSISHard on the ML-DSA half keeping the transcript unforgeable; the downgrade fails unless BOTH floors fall. Teeth (Suite=Bool, classical=false<hybrid=true, toy sig=(pk,m)): honest handshake AGREES on the strongest common (hybrid) + A accepts; the authenticated downgrade to classical EXHIBITS the Forgery via the full downgrade_forces_forgery on concrete data (provable HonestSigner); and — LOAD-BEARING — an UNAUTHENTICATED negotiation (accept = "I support it", no sig) IS freely downgradable (both accept classical though strongest is hybrid), so the transcript authentication is exactly what buys downgrade resistance. #assert_all_clean (11 keystones).
import Dregg2.Crypto.ConsensusSafety -- the FIRST step UP from crypto primitives to protocol SOUNDNESS: CONSENSUS SAFETY as a crypto game — two conflicting blocks cannot both be finalized. The crypto sibling of Consensus.Safety (which carries the honesty law abstractly over a BFTModel): here the honesty law is DERIVED from (a) honest-supermajority quorum intersection + (b) the unforgeability of the HYBRID-SIGNED finalization votes. Model: a committee of n members (≤ f Byzantine, n > 3f), a FinalizationVote is a HybridCombiner.SigScheme signature by a member over voteMsg(height‖block); a block is Finalized at a height when a quorum of q = n − f distinct members hold valid votes. §1 two_quorums_share_honest — pure Finset counting (|A∩B| ≥ |A|+|B|−n via card_union_add_card_inter, then |(A∩B)\byz| ≥ n−3f ≥ 1): any two quorums share ≥1 HONEST member. §2 no_two_conflicting_finalized — two conflicting blocks both finalized ⇒ an honest member holds valid votes for BOTH; either it never cast one (a fresh valid sig on an un-queried body = a HybridCombiner.Forgery refuting its EufCma) or it double-voted (forbidden by the honest-voting rule, stated explicitly). §3 consensus_safe_under_floor — the votes ARE the ed25519∧ML-DSA hybrid, so each honest member's EufCma is DISCHARGED by HybridCombiner.hybrid_secure_if_either_floor: safety holds under (n>3f) ∧ (SchnorrDLHard ∨ MSISHard) — QUANTUM-SAFE FINALITY, the protocol-level payoff of the whole hybrid campaign; no named-carrier laundering (only the two floors + the threshold + the honest-voting rule are irreducible, the forking reductions are hypotheses). Teeth: n=4,f=1,q=3 two quorums share ≥2≥1 honest member; threshold_is_load_bearing (at n=3f the honest overlap is EMPTY — safety fails without n>3f); a double vote by a member that signed one block IS a Forgery; and without EufCma/the honest rule BOTH conflicting blocks finalize (tooth_eufcma_is_load_bearing). #assert_all_clean (8 keystones).
